  "prompt": "Are there any hotels in Goa which could be safe for unmarried couples?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several hotels in Goa that are welcoming to unmarried couples. Many hotels and resorts in popular tourist areas like North Goa and South Goa have policies that accommodate unmarried couples. Here are a few tips to consider when looking for accommodations:\n\n1. **Check Reviews:** Look for hotels that are specifically mentioned in reviews as being couple-friendly.\n\n2. **Book with Couples in Mind:** Some hotels explicitly state that they accept unmarried couples. You can search for \"couple-friendly hotels\" in Goa.\n\n3. **Avoid Local Guest Houses:** Some local guest houses may have strict policies, so it's generally safer to opt for well-known chains or established hotels.\n\n4. **Check Policies:** Before booking, check the hotel\u2019s policy on unmarried couples, which can usually be found on their official website or by calling the hotel directly.\n\n5. **Look Beyond Traditional Hotels:** Some serviced apartments or homestays may also be open to unmarried couples, offering more privacy and flexibility.\n\nHotels like ITC Grand Goa, Novotel Goa, and Treebo Hotels often have policies that embrace guests regardless of marital status. Always ensure to provide valid identification during check-in.",
